React.js is a *JavaScript library for building user interfaces*, especially single-page apps. Created by Meta, it focuses on components, speed, and interactivity.

*1ï¸âƒ£ What is React?*  
React lets you build reusable *UI components* and update the DOM efficiently using a *virtual DOM*.

*Why Use React?*  
â€¢ Reusable components  
â€¢ Faster performance with virtual DOM  
â€¢ Great for building SPAs (Single Page Applications)  
â€¢ Strong community and ecosystem  

*2ï¸âƒ£ Key Concepts*  

*ğŸ“¦ Components* â€“ Reusable, independent pieces of UI.  
```jsx
function Welcome() {
  return <h1>Hello, React!</h1>;
}
```

*ğŸ§  Props* â€“ Pass data to components  
```jsx
function Greet(props) {
  return <h2>Hello, {props.name}!</h2>;
}
<Greet name="Riya" />
```

*ğŸ’¡ State* â€“ Store and manage data in a component  
```jsx
import { useState } from 'react';

function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  return (
    <>
      <p>Count: {count}</p>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Add</button>
    </>
  );
}
```

*3ï¸âƒ£ Hooks*  

*useState* â€“ Manage local state  
*useEffect* â€“ Run side effects (like API calls, DOM updates)  
```jsx
import { useEffect } from 'react';

useEffect(() => {
  console.log("Component mounted");
}, []);
```

*4ï¸âƒ£ JSX*  
JSX lets you write HTML inside JS.  
```jsx
const element = <h1>Hello World</h1>;
```

*5ï¸âƒ£ Conditional Rendering*  
```jsx
{isLoggedIn ? <Dashboard /> : <Login />}
```

*6ï¸âƒ£ Lists and Keys*  
```jsx
const items = ["Apple", "Banana"];
items.map((item, index) => <li key={index}>{item}</li>);
```

*7ï¸âƒ£ Event Handling*  
```jsx
<button onClick={handleClick}>Click Me</button>
```

*8ï¸âƒ£ Form Handling*  
```jsx
<input value={name} onChange={(e) => setName(e.target.value)} />
```

*9ï¸âƒ£ React Router (Bonus)*  
To handle multiple pages  
```bash
npm install react-router-dom
```
```jsx
import { BrowserRouter, Route, Routes } from 'react-router-dom';
```

